                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#172va">Fol. 172va</locus>-vb: Donation note extended by a genealogy of the donor.<q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 172va-vb: አቡነ፡ ተላዌ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወለደ፡ አቡነ፡ ንዋየ፡ ማርያም፡ ኃይለ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለተ፡ ቀለምሲስ፡ ወለደ፡ ወለተ፡ ቀለምሲስ፡ አቡነ፡ ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወለደት፡ ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወእኁሁ፡ ኃይለ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወወልዱ፡ ወልዱ[sic]፡ ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወምስለ፡ ብእ[fol. 172vb]ሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሕይወት፡ ወምስለ፡ እሙ፡ ኡጽፍተ፡ ድንግል፡ ወምስለ፡ እኅቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ኪዳን፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘተሳየጣ፡ በንዋዩ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘወሐቦ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ሰጣ[sic]፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ወዘተአገላ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ይኩን፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።[fol. 173r] ከመ፡ ይኩኖሙ፡ መርሐ፡ መንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 172va-vb: ʾabunä Tälawe Krǝstos begot ʾabunä Nǝwayä Maryam, Ḫaylä Maryam, Wälättä Qälämsis, he begot (them). Wälättä Qälämsis begot ʾabunä Wäldä Śǝllase, Wäldä Śǝllase Gäbrä Mikaʾel and his brother Ḫaylä Mikaʾel, and his son Wäldä Mikaʾel, with his wife Wälättä Ḥǝywät, and with his mother ʾUṣǝftä Dǝngǝl, and with his sister Wälättä Kidan. ʾAbunä Gäbrä Mikaʾel bought this book with his own money and donated it to (the tabot of) St. Michael of Säṭa. He who stole it or erased (its text) shall be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul, for ever and ever, amen. So that it might be for them a guide (to) the Kingdom of Heaven.</q>
                           The note ends in the upper margin of the following folio. ʾAbunä Gäbrä Mikaʾel is indicated as the son of ʾabunä Wäldä Śǝllase in Additio 4.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6"> <locus target="#183ra">Fols. 183ra-185</locus>vb; 1va-2vb; 122vb-124vb; 171ra-172rb: Anaphora of St. Basil of Caesarea.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The text of the Anaphora continues from fols. 183ra-185vb onto fols. 1va-2vb, 122vb-124vb and 171ra-172r. The text is incomplete: there is a lacuna between the text portions on fols. 185vb and 1va (possible one leaf missing). The text is written in a slightly smaller script than the rest of the Anaphoras, in a secondary hand (careful, but somewhat irregular as compared with the main hand).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude notes (writing exercises): fols. 1r, 2r, 4r.&#xD;
- Pen trial, in red ink: fol. 1v, in the bottom margin.&#xD;
- Omitted passages written in the margin (sometimes the place the passages belongs to is indicated by the tämälläs-sigh in the shape of the cross, written in the text column; but sometimes there is no visible sign): fols. 5r, 9v, 97r, 141r, in the upper margin, 24ra, in the bottom margin, etc.&#xD;
- Crude notes (both recent and older): fols. 8r, 40r, 41r, 44r, 46r, 47v, etc., in the upper margin.&#xD;
- Extensive crude notes (apparently writing exercise): fols. 83v-84r, in the bottom margin.&#xD;
- The names of the donors are also indicated in supplication formulas within the text of the Ms. (s. fols. 7vb-8ra, 26vb, 28vb, etc.).</item>
